description:
&lt;p&gt;This post is only open to current employees of University Hospitals of Morecambe Bay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen in Morecambe Bay to join the Postgraduate Medical Education team based at the Education Centre Royal Lancaster Infirmary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic individual who is able to demonstrate the ability to work with a multiple number of teams with a high level of attention to detail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work closely with trainers, trainees and teaching staff and provide administrative support to the Director of Medical Education and other senior medical colleagues in the coordination of medical education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will also work closely with an experienced administrative staff both within Medical Education and other education teams external to the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will also provide ‘front of house’ services including room bookings, dealing with enquiries from users, preparing teaching rooms and maintaining the daily activities of the education centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anyone newly appointed to the trust will be subject to the completion of a satisfactory 6 month probationary period (this includes bank staff). This will give the new staff member an opportunity to become familiar with the role and working environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A short skills test will be undertaken at interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal queries about the post are welcome.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
